a.title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.
a.xlink:title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.

a.title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.
a.xlink:title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.

a.title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.
a.xlink:title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― ConceptSystemCorrespondence: Relationship between 2 or more concept systems described through mapping similarity relationships between their member concepts.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystemCorrespondence: Relationship between 2 or more concept systems described through mapping similarity relationships between their member concepts.

a.title: ― CorrespondenceTable: Set of relationships between the members within or between statistical classifications.
